<!-- SEO ARTICLE -->
<section class="article-section fade-in">
<div class="container">
<div class="article-body">
<h2>The complete guide to e-commerce fulfillment services: what is included and what to ask</h2>
<p>Choosing a fulfillment provider is one of the most consequential decisions an e-commerce business makes. The wrong partner can destroy your customer experience; the right one can unlock growth you cannot achieve alone. Here is what you need to understand about modern fulfillment services.</p>
<h3>What a fulfillment per-order price actually covers</h3>
<p>Fulfillment pricing can be opaque. At MTP Group, the per-order price (from 18 UAH at 200+ orders/day) includes a specific set of operations: retrieving the item from its warehouse bin, scanning the barcode to verify accuracy, packing into an appropriately sized box with protective materials, printing and applying the carrier waybill, and handing the sealed package to Nova Poshta during one of four daily pickups. WMS access, packing materials, and labels are included in this price. Storage, goods receiving, and co-packing are separate line items. Understanding this breakdown prevents surprises on your first invoice.</p>
<h3>The auto-callback system: a uniquely Ukrainian advantage</h3>
<p>In mature e-commerce markets, nearly all orders are prepaid. In Ukraine, roughly 60% of online purchases are cash-on-delivery. This creates a unique problem: buyers who place orders but never collect them. The no-show rate can reach 15-20%, turning profitable orders into costly returns. MTP Group's automated callback robot contacts buyers within minutes of order placement to confirm their purchase intent. Across our client base, this simple technology increases the buyout rate by 10-15%, directly improving your bottom line at a cost of just 0.50 UAH per call.</p>
<h3>Photo documentation: accountability at every stage</h3>
<p>Professional fulfillment providers photograph goods at critical stages: when inventory arrives at the warehouse (to document factory condition), when returns are inspected (to verify buyer claims and determine restockability), and during dispute resolution (to support carrier damage claims). At MTP Group, all photos are timestamped and accessible through your WMS dashboard. This creates an audit trail that resolves customer disputes faster and reduces your exposure to fraudulent return claims.</p>
<h3>Dynamic pricing: how scaling reduces your cost per order</h3>
<p>The most powerful feature of modern fulfillment pricing is its inverse relationship with volume. At MTP Group, a client shipping 5 orders per day pays 26 UAH per order. At 50 orders, the rate drops to 22 UAH. At 200+, it reaches 18 UAH. These tier adjustments happen automatically based on your trailing 30-day average &mdash; no contract renegotiation, no manual requests. This means every marketing campaign you run that increases order volume also decreases your per-unit logistics cost. Growth becomes self-reinforcing.</p>
<h3>International outbound shipping: selling Ukrainian goods abroad</h3>
<p>While most of our clients ship within Ukraine, an increasing number use our warehouse as a hub for international e-commerce. Ukrainian-made goods &mdash; natural cosmetics, handcrafted products, specialty foods, IT hardware &mdash; ship to EU, US, and UK buyers via UPS, DHL, and Meest. Our team prepares customs documentation, prints international waybills, and handles carrier handoff. This two-way capability makes MTP Group a full-service logistics partner for both inbound and outbound cross-border commerce.</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>

